               <msContents class="#CM">
                  <summary><p>The palm-leaf bundle, a composite manuscript, entitled <title xml:lang="ta">Viratam Mūṉṟu</title> on its additional title page, contains:
  <list rend="numbered">
  <item>The <title xml:lang="ta">Manōṉmaṉiyantāti</title> (Indien 5a).</item>
  <item>The <title xml:lang="ta">Vināyakaruṭaiya Mūlātārattiṉuṭaiya Uyir</title> (Indien 5b).</item>
  <item><foreign xml:lang="sa">Mantra</foreign>s and <foreign xml:lang="sa">cakkaram</foreign>s (Indien 5c).</item>
  </list>
</p>
<p>The bundle also contains:
<list>
  <item>A title page folio (U1).</item>
  <item>A diagram (U2).</item>
  <item>A stanza (U3).</item>
  <item>A back guard leaf (U4).</item>
  </list>
  U2 and U3 are found between Indien 5a and Indien 5b and might be part of either.
</p>
   <p>Description based on the digital images available on Gallica.</p>  <p>Dimensions after Cabaton (1912).</p>      </summary>
                  
                  
